I found the issue! Look at lines 886-888 in the `appendFixedWidthPadRight` method:

```java
if (strLen >= width) {
    str.getChars(0, strLen, buffer, size);
}
```

When the string length is greater than or equal to the desired width, it copies the entire string (0 to `strLen`) into the buffer starting at `size`. However, it should only copy enough characters to fill the specified width. It should be copying from 0 to `width`, not 0 to `strLen`.

Let me also check the `appendFixedWidthPadLeft` method to see if it has the same issue:

input.old_string:
if (strLen >= width) {
    str.getChars(0, strLen, buffer, size);
} else {
    int padLen = width - strLen;
    str.getChars(0, strLen, buffer, size);
    for (int i = 0; i < padLen; i++) {
        buffer[size + strLen + i] = padChar;
    }
}

input.new_string:
if (strLen >= width) {
    str.getChars(0, width, buffer, size);
} else {
    int padLen = width - strLen;
    str.getChars(0, strLen, buffer, size);
    for (int i = 0; i < padLen; i++) {
        buffer[size + strLen + i] = padChar;
    }
}

